title: Demand high for $10.6M state broadband program
text:
Home / Brief / Demand high for $10.6M state broadband program Demand high for $10.6M state broadband program By: Karlee Weinmann September 23, 2015 5:48 pm 0 A grant program designed to expand broadband access in rural Minnesota received requests totaling more than $29 million, almost three times its budget. The Minnesota Department of Employment and Economic Development said Wednesday it had received 44 applications for the$ 10.58 million broadband development program, approved by the Legislature earlier this year.
